      "date": "2017-06-02 18:20:46.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> (1 comment)\n > \n > When are we switching to 3.x?\n\n3.1 is just some version in the future - long enough to give apps warning about this ioctl, but not so far that we never get there.  We could always delete it earlier if we never move to 3.x, but I wanted to make sure that it is eventually deleted automatically rather than being kept forever like CFG_F_COMPAT146 or LDD_F_UPGRADE14 which were introduced in 2007 for 1.4->1.6 compatibility and never removed.",
